@startmindmap
* SLH-DSA (FIPS 205)
** Context
*** Stateless hash-based signature
*** Standardized SPHINCS+
*** Published 13 Aug 2024
*** Most conservative PQC choice
** Security
*** Hash preimage/collision only
*** No lattice / number theory
*** EUF-CMA up to 2^64 signatures
*** n = 16/24/32 -> cat 1/3/5
left side
** Building blocks
*** WOTS+ : one-time (hash chains + checksum)
*** XMSS : 2^h' uses via Merkle tree
*** Hypertree : d layers of XMSS
*** FORS : few-time, signs the digest
** Keys
*** SK = (SK.seed, SK.prf, PK.seed, PK.root) = 4n
*** PK = (PK.seed, PK.root) = 2n
*** PK.root = top XMSS root
*** pk only 32/48/64 bytes
** Signing
*** R = PRF_msg(SK.prf, opt_rand, M)
*** digest = H_msg(R, PK.seed, PK.root, M)
*** md -> FORS, idx_tree/idx_leaf
*** FORS sign -> PK_FORS
*** ht_sign certifies PK_FORS
*** SIG = R || SIG_FORS || SIG_HT
*** no rejection loop
** Verification
*** recompute digest + indices
*** rebuild PK_FORS from SIG_FORS
*** ht_verify up d layers
*** accept iff root = PK.root
** Parameters
*** 12 sets = 6 x (SHA2 / SHAKE)
*** s = small sig, slow sign
*** f = fast sign, big sig
*** sig 7856 .. 49856 bytes
** Variants
*** Hedged (default) vs deterministic
*** Pure vs HashSLH-DSA
*** domain separator + context
@endmindmap
